& [IntendedPurpose] is the mathematical target shape
  + [purpose] is relate analytic vanishing of an elliptic curve L-function to algebraic rank of rational points
  + [analytic_side] is order of vanishing of L(E,s) at the central point
  + [algebraic_side] is rank of E(Q), the finitely generated group of rational points
  + [bridge_need] is a controlled correspondence from analytic collapse to algebraic generator structure

& [DocumentProposition] is the source-implied proposition
  + [raw_shape] is L-hand collapse marks the L-function zero while R-hand growth unfolds rational-point structure
  + [candidate_receptive_form] is analytic vanishing may be treated as a collapse signature whose multiplicity predicts the independent algebraic directions available for rational-point generation
  + [meaning_role] is a dual-aspect bridge between analytic degeneracy and algebraic emergence
  + [proof_status] is inquiry_candidate_not_proof

& [PeripheryTrigger] is the curiosity trigger
  + [trigger_type] is mixed accumulation_trigger and heat_zone_crossing_trigger
  + [accumulation_signal] is repeated document pattern of collapse/growth, phase correction, rational directions, and structure-over-enumeration
  + [heat_zone_crossing] is crossing from symbolic handedness language into an actual analytic/algebraic duality in BSD
  + [restraint_gate] is proof-status boundary and formal arithmetic-geometry mapping requirement

