& [BetterProblemShape] is the improved shape after first probe
  + [original_shape] is prove BSD by symbolic collapse/growth resonance
  + [adjusted_shape] is investigate whether the collapse/growth frame can organize a traceable mapping between analytic rank, algebraic rank, generator emergence, and refined leading-term data
  + [narrowed_proposition] is L-hand/R-hand language is promising if it can be grounded in rank, generators, height/regulator behavior, and L-function leading-term structure
  + [proof_obligation_001] is define the map from zero order to independent rational directions without circularly assuming BSD
  + [proof_obligation_002] is explain how R-hand growth identifies or constructs Mordell-Weil generators
  + [proof_obligation_003] is account for refined BSD data beyond rank, including regulator, torsion, Tamagawa factors, and Tate-Shafarevich group if the proposition claims full BSD
